comments.message:
Please take a look at how we generally write these.  We try to avoid the json_pointer thing.  Return the translated interface into the calling scope, and let the calling scope both deal with errors and figure out where to put this in the tree

something like

std::string locationType = getLocationType(interface);
if (locationType.empty()){
   internal error....
}
asyncResp->res[Location] = locationType;

This keeps the method calls simple, and gives each handler the ability to manage its own errors, which tend to be different.
